Text: Important EFile Reminder from TurboTaxDear TurboTax Customer The status of your electronically filed federal tax return is now available from the IRS You must view this status to determine whether or not the IRS has accepted your return To get your status TurboTax software users Open your TurboTax program and well show you how to obtain the status of any returns you have filed electronically TurboTax for the Web users Log on to TurboTax for the Web and well show you how to obtain the status of any returns you have filed electronically If the IRS has accepted your electronically filed return TurboTax will walk you through the remaining tasks you must complete before the IRS considers your tax return officially filed and complete Please follow the instructions in TurboTax carefully If your return is rejected you must fix the errors in your return and retransmit your return for approval NOTE If you have filed a state return electronically you will receive a separate email notification once TurboTax has received the status from the state taxing authority For more information on how to check the status of your return please refer to the Help section of TurboTax Thank you for using TurboTax Please Note Please do not respond to this email address This email address is used only by TurboTax automated systems and is not monitored This email was notification requested by you when you prepared your tax return with TurboTax
